      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Upper body shot of a Catholic peasant boy and girl talking at the tram station in <ref target="http://gams.uni-graz.at/o:siba.glossar?mode=B4">Baščaršija</ref>. They are wearing Sunday attire, including a dark fur cap (šubara) on the boy’s head, while the girl has a white scarf fixed in her plaited hair. A tram waggon is seen in the background surrounded by people, among them soldiers in Royal Yugoslav Army uniform.</ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet" subtype="comment">The loose white scarf indicates an unmarried girl. The costumes are from the surroundings of Sarajevo. Analogue photographic process, negative-positive (Agfa Isopan 17 DIN). Original preserved as a negative and a positive on silver bromine paper, stored as a negative, print and digital record.</ab>
